content: بالامانه المكان سيء جدا لا يرتقي ان يحمل اسم منتزه الملك سلمان. مكان الجلسات غير مكتمله البناء. حفريات غير مكتمله ولا مدفونه. طبيعة الارض حجريه يصعب الجلوس عليها. دورات المياه مغلقه او لا يوجد ماء. قبل فتره اقفلت للصيانه ثم فتحت ولم الاحظ اي تغيير او تحسين. لا مظلات او تشجير. المكان بعيد من المدينه والخدمات. بنظري اقرب مخطط فاضي افضل من الذهاب الى المنتزه.

content: عين موسى المياه تفور بشكل دائم وغير منقطع من الرمال في بلدة مقنا وهي المدينة الساحلية الحالمة على خليج نيوم بمنطقة تبوك شمال غربي السعودية وتبعد مقنا عن منطقة تبوك 235 كلم، وتشتهر بمناظر خلابة وزراعات متعددة، من بينها المانجو الشهيرة في صاحبة الإطلالة الأجمل على خليج العقبة، حيث تطل من بين جبلين عملاقين عبر وادي مقنا الذي يصب بالخليج الأعمق في العالم ، وتعتبر مقنا ميناء قديم وهي من أقدم الموانئ في المنطقة، وكان يستخدم قديما للسفر من خلاله من وإلى جمهورية مصر العربية. أما العيون الموجودة التي لم يتبق منها إلا عين واحدة، فهي عين موسى التي أكدها المؤرخون. وعلينا أن نتوجه للسياحة والآثار بالاهتمام والعناية بالقرية التي تمتلك مقومات سياحية طبيعية وأثرية .

content: Umm Lajj One of the best beaches in Saudi Arabia It's one of the beautiful & cleanest beaches I have seen It was open for Public in 2015,nearing completion The beach is open and wide with small huts for public and swings for children. The water is clear but is a bit salty. The place is quite and clean There is not much around except for the beaches and hotels But it's a must visit for anyone on an enroute The city is serene and beautiful, population is not too much here & hardly any locals around . Beach is a relaxing spot perfect to visit in the evening . This beach will give you all an Instagram worthy shots. One of the drawback is that once you miss a u turn it will take kilometers to get the next one Expats are mostly around this beach There are also some sculptures on around the beach It's definitely worth visiting If u loved this review make sure to give it a big thumbs up. Peace

I encourage everyone to visit this place once in your life. Lastly, keep the Crater cleaner than when you arrived. Keep Saudi sites crystal clean so everyone can enjoy and appreciate its beauty. So, Pick up your trash and dispose of it properly outside the Crater. Thank you for Keeping KSA clean 😊

content: قلعة مارد تحكيم بين على بن طالب اللغةتنزيل بصيغة PDFراقبعدل قلعة مارد هي قلعة تاريخية حربية تقع بمدينة دومة الجندل بمنطقة الجوف، وتبعد عن مدينة سكاكا حوالي 50 كم[1]، ويعود تاريخها إلى القرن الأول الميلادي،[2] وأقدم ذكر لها يعود للقرن الثالث الميلادي حيث ذكرتها الملكة الزباء (240 - 274) حينما غزت دومة الجندل وتيماء ولم تستطع اقتحام القلعة فقالت: "تمرد مارد وعز الأبلق".[3] قلعة مارد منظر داخلي لقلعة مارد إحداثيات29.4840°N 39.5202°Eمعلومات عامةنوع المبنىقلعةالدولة السعودية قلعة مارد تعديل مصدري - تعديل الموقع والتسميةعدل تقع القلعة على ربوة ارتفاعها 620 م تقريباً فوق سطح البحر[4]، وتطل على مدينة دومة الجندل التابعة لمنطقة الجوف من الجهة الغربية، وهو ما ساهم في قوة تحصينها حيث يستطيع المطل من القلعة أن يشرف على جميع أجزاء البلدة ويرى القادم إليها من مسافات بعيدة.[5] سميت قلعة مارد بهذا الاسم لتمردها واستعصائها على من يحاول اقتحامها كما ذكر ياقوت الحموي.[2][3] تاريخ القلعةعدل استخدم المبنى مقراً وقصر للحكم، أما فيما يخص أقدم ذكر للقلعة فيعود لملكة تدمر زنوبيا (الزباء) في القرن الثالث الميلادي 267-272م، عندما غزت دومة الجندل ولكنها فشلت في اقتحام قلعة مارد واتجهت إلى تيماء ولكنها أيضا لم تستطع اقتحامها فقالت مقولتها الشهيرة:(تمرد مارد وعز الأبلق) إلا أن الدلائل الأثرية ومن خلال المجسمات التي أجريت داخل القلعة وخارجها تظهر أنها استخدمت في الفترة النبطية أو أن أجزاء منها بنيت في هذه الفترة واستمر استخدامها في صدر الإسلام حتى الفترات الحديثة. وصف القلعة والتنقيب وصف القلعة والتنقيبعدلالقلعة مستطيلة الشكل في الأصل لكنها الآن بيضاوية الشكل، ويمكن الدخول إليها من مدخلين رئيسيين أحدهم في جنوب القلعة والآخر في الشمال بجانب البرج، وتتكون القلعة من طابقين حيث بني السفلي من الحجارة والعلوي من الطين كما توجد أربعة أبراج مخروطية الشكل استحدثت في أزمنة مختلفة بارتفاع 12 متر تقريباً، ويوجد بداخل القلعة بئران وتضم طوابقه غرفاً للحرس والرماية والمراقبة، ويحيط بالقلعة سور كبير من الحجر بهِ العديد من الفتحات للمراقبة، وللسور مدخلان الأول من جهة الجنوب والآخر من جهة الشمال، كما يحتاج زائر القلعة إلى نصف ساعة للصعود إلى أعلى القلعة عبر درج يضم 1000 درجة ملتوية.[6] ويوجد في القلعة أربعة أبراج مخروطية الشكل في جهاته الأربع وبفناء الحصن مجموعة من الغرب الطينية تقع في الجهة الشمالية الشرقية والجنوبية الشرقية التي تستخدم في بنائها الطوب اللبن وهي من المباني المضافة وفي الجهة الشمالية الغربية يوجد مبنى من الحجر مكون من دورين، والحصن مبني من الحجر (الجندل)، أما المباني الطينية في الأجزاء العلوية منه سواء على الجدران الداخلية أو الخارجية أو الاأراج فهي من المباني المضافة إلى القلعة.[7] أثبتت أعمال الحفر في قلعة مارد -داخل القلعة وخارجها- أن القلعة تعود إلى العصر النبطي؛ حيث أسفرت عمليات الحفر عن وجود طبقات أثرية وكسر فخارية تعود للعصر النبطي، إلى جانب عدد من المعثورات والاكتشافات الأثرية التي تؤرخ للعصر النبطي، وهي: أساسات قلعة مارد الضخمة.طبقات أثرية نبطية في أنحاء مختلفة من دومة الجندلمجموعة من المقابر النبطية الجماعية في موقع يسمى (الصنيميات) الواقع غرب دومة الجندلبقايا سور قلعة مارد.[8] أعيد بناء بعض أجزاء القلعة بين سنتي 1416 للهجرة و1423 للهجرة.[2][9] إضافة إلى مشروع ترميم للمسجد يشمل أجزاء من حي الدرع، تضمن تركيب مبان حجرية وترميم شروخ الواجهات والمدخل والممرات، وتركيب أسقف خشبية من جذوع الأثل في الممرات وطبقات عازلة للرطوبة. وفي سنة 1976 كشفت الحفريات وعمليات التنقيب عن خزفيات نبطية ورومانية تعود للقرن الميلادي الأول والثاني.[3] وقامت فرقة تنقيب بالانتهاء من التنقيب في شرق القلعة والسور.[10] الصور

content: بدأت المياه تفور بشكل دائم وغير منقطع من الرمال في مقنا، وهي المدينة الساحلية الحالمة على خليج العقبة، بمنطقة تبوك شمال غربي السعودية. "مقنا" تبعد عن منقطة تبوك 235 كلم، وتشتهر بمناظر خلابة وزراعات متعددة، من بينها المانجو الشهيرة في صاحبة الإطلالة الأجمل على خليج العقبة، حيث تطل من بين جبلين عملاقين عبر وادي مقنا الذي يصب بالخليج الأعمق في العالم. وفي وادي مقنا، وقبيل الساحل بكيلومترات بسيطة، تتشابك أشجار النخيل حول عيون فوارة، يسميها أهالي المنطقة بعيون موسى، ويسمونها أيضاً بالقدر، نسبة لفوارن القدر على النار. #عيون_موسى وهي عيون تنبع في #وادي_مقنا الشهير، عبر 6 فتحات بالرمال، تحركها المياه التي تنبع من باطن الأرض جميع سكان مقنا عايشوا هذه العيون الجارية منذ طفولتهم وهكذا حديث آبائهم عنها.

content: إثراء ليس مجرد مكان بل هو تجربة متكاملة اوقات الزيارة من ايام الاسبوع من الساعه التاسعه صباحا إلى الثانية عشرة صباحا. الجمعة من الساعه الرابعة مساء إلى الثانية عشر صباحا. الأحد مغلق. مركز إثراء سيأخذكم في تجربه فريدة من نوعها حيث طبيعة المكان الجبلية تبعدك عن ازعاج المدينة. روعه تصميم المكان بالارصفة و أشجار النخيل والزهور ونظافة المكان تعطي شعور الأماكن السياحية الجميلة. جميع الموظفين ودودين ومتواجدين بشكل مستمر لاستفساراتكم. فعاليات إثراء من ورش العمل وهي ورشة الرسم و ورشة صنع الفخار وورشة النجارة والمسرح والمكتبة كلها تقدم لكم مجانا وبسفة دائما انصح الجميع بتجربة هذة الفعاليات. بصراحة إبداع بمعنى الكلمه مركز الطاقه تم تحديثه ليصبح تفاعلي اكثر مع تقدم التكنولوجيا الجميع سيحظي بتجربة فريدة من نوعها.

content: That is the best place for vacation, rest & recreation, we enjoyed all family specially my children, we all very much love the mountains, specially 💓 that green mountains, it is 180 km from Jizam my home, just after 2 hours drive you can not imagine that you are in Saudi Arabia, because of beautiful cool weather, there minimum Temp. I found in June minimum 12 in night and feel as winter with cold winds, and 24 in day in sunlight, feel same as in winter, we found ±3° to ±7° in month of January, December. many weekend we enjoyed at their, remember that food and restaurant will be closed quickly in evening, ypi not wait as other areas of Saudia, also closed in day time if weather is raining and highly cool. Remember be careful to drive in raining, better to stay in raining, and use standard highway to reach Soudah mountain, dont go GPS shortest way, if you are not resident of mountains, and you can go with your 4 cylinder small car, but dont select the way of Shuban Alma track, there are many peaks, hard for small car. content: Nice historical site to visit if you are in the area. The wreckage is from the 60's. The fuselage is eroded with a separated tail segment and some missing part. This was a WWII surplus plane flown to the area by an American. The site is protected now but you can see graffiti on the some parts. The beach next to it is fantastic and you can see Egypt in the far distance (my phone actually connected to Egyptian cell network while here). Plan to explore the plane and have a picnic at the nearby beach. Bring sandals as the area around the plane floods with tide

content: Umm Lajj One of the best beaches in Saudi Arabia It's one of the beautiful & cleanest beaches I have seen It was open for Public in 2015,nearing completion The beach is open and wide with small huts for public and swings for children. The water is clear but is a bit salty. The place is quite and clean There is not much around except for the beaches and hotels But it's a must visit for anyone on an enroute The city is serene and beautiful, population is not too much here & hardly any locals around . Beach is a relaxing spot perfect to visit in the evening . This beach will give you all an Instagram worthy shots. One of the drawback is that once you miss a u turn it will take kilometers to get the next one Expats are mostly around this beach There are also some sculptures on around the beach It's definitely worth visiting If u loved this review make sure to give it a big thumbs up. Peace

content: أبها هي الدليل الحي على أن السياحة في السعودية لها عدة أوجه أخرى ممتعة، بخلاف السياحة الدينية الغالبة على المشهد. فمدينة أبها زاخرة بالطبيعة الجميلة، والمتمثلة في الجبال والسهول الخضراء، ولكن أكثر ما يستقطب السياح داخلها، هي المتنزهات، ويأتي متنزه أبو خيال الواقع على الطريق الدائري للمدينة، كواحد من أجمل الاماكن السياحية في أبها. سيضعك منتزه أبو خيال داخل لوحة طبيعية خلابة، فهو من أفضل الاماكن السياحية في أبها للعوائل؛ حيث سيتمتع أطفالك بالمساحات الخضراء الشاسعة، والملاعب، وسط مجموعة متنوعة من النباتات والحيوانات. أما في حالة رغبت في تناول وجبة شهية بصحبة عائلتك، هناك مطعماً داخله، يقدم أكلات مميزة وبأسعار في متناول يدك، لذلك يعتبر من أفضل منتزهات أبها.

content: The park is comprised of 4 kids play area, 2 prayer area separate for men and women and two separate restrooms. The park is best suited for families with kids and babies. There is a separate track for people who are interested in walking and jogging. The park is spacious and have more than two entrances. All the entrances supports wheelchair accessibility. There are four wheelchair accessible parking spaces reserved for people with disability. The slides here are in good condition but need maintenance. The park gets very crowded especially in the weekends. There are few local vendors in the park selling the goods for kids and babies. Covid19 prevention protocol: No body temperature is checked by the security at the park entrance. Masks are must to enter the premises of the park but no one is checking on this. No social distancing is maintained inside the park.

content: مكان رائع جدًا يتّسم حي البجيري بقيمة تاريخية حيث كان الحي مقراً لسكن الشيخ محمد بن عبدالوهاب رحمه الله، وأسرته، إضافة إلى ما يتميز به الحي من موقع استراتيجي مميز لتوسطه بلدة الدرعية التاريخية وكونه المدخل الرئيسي لحي الطريف، إضافة إلى إطلالته المميزة على وادي حنيفة. وتهدف مشاريع التطوير المستمرة في حي البجيري، إلى إبراز قيمة الحي التاريخية عبر تطوير منشآته الثقافية والعمرانية، وتوظيف عناصره المختلفة، لخدمة الأهداف العامة لبرنامج تطوير الدرعية التاريخية، ومن أبرز عناصر مشروع تطوير حي البجيري مقر مؤسسة الشيخ محمد بن عبدالوهاب الثقافية والتي تهدف المؤسسة إلى التعريف بدعوة الشيخ محمد بن عبدالوهاب، رحمه الله، وتأكيد دور المملكة القيادي في العالم الإسلامي.

content: Al Masmak is a thick-walled fortress that was established in Riyadh during the second Saudi state time in the 19th century. It was built mainly for defense purposes, but later had different uses. After the fall of the second Saudi State, members of the Saudi royal family including, Abdulaziz ibn Saud (father of the current king), left Riyadh to live in Kuwait. Abdulaziz, who later baceme king, wanted to take back Riyadh from Ibn Rasheed. He had several attempts to recapture Riyadh but he did not succeed until his last attempt on an early morning of January 1902 (1319 AH). On that morning, Abdulaziz ibn Saud and his men reached Riyadh managed to recapture Riyadh from the chief of Riyadh at that time “ibn Ajlan” in a battle known today as The Battle Of Riyadh right at Al Masmak Fort. This battle was the starting point for re-unifying the different emirates and tribes of the arabian peninsula. which makes Al Masmak one of the most iconic places in Saudi Arabia's modern history. After the recapture of Riyadh; Al Masmak was used as a town hall and then served as a warehouse for munitions. What most people might not know about Al masmak is, that not too long after being used as a warehouse, the fort served as a prison until mid 20th century. Nowadays, Al-Masmak is a museum that covers the history of The kingdom with more focus on Riyadh and the battle of Riyadh. The museum contains artifacts, weapons, maps, a small theater showing the story of the Battle of Riyadh and a really good photo-gallery that gives visitors a brief insight of how life in Riyadh looked like in the first half of the 20th century. Al Masmak was built on top of a strong rocky foundation using local building substances such as clay, palm tree materials, straw, rocks and tamarix trunks. The fortress is one of few, well perserved mud buildings in Riyadh, which makes it a very good illustration of traditional najdi architecture. It is one of the kingdoms must visit museums and it’s free Entry.
title: Al Masmak Palace Museum

content: جبل القارة ويُعرَف أيضاً بجبل الشبعان يقع بين قرية التويثير وقرية القارة بمحافظة الأحساء، في المنطقة الشرقية من المملكة العربية السعودية. يُعد الجبل من أبرز المعالم السياحية الطبيعية في الأحساء وقد سُجل في لائحة التراث العالمي عام 2018م بعد ضم واحة الأحساء إلى اللائحة. يبعد الجبل مسافة 15 كيلومتراً شرق مدينة الهفوف. ويحتوي على كهوفٍ أو ما يسمى بالمغاراتِ بين أهالي الأحساء. تتميز بعض مغاراته مثل مغارة النشاب بأن لها درجة حرارة معتدلة شبه ثابتة طوال العام. سعر تذكرة الدخول 50 ريال

content: Qara Mountain is the perfect place to visit when you are seeking family adventure. On the outside, the view of the mountains are breathtaking. Then on the inside, there are many tunnels and exploring through them, was incredibly fun. Even though, they are open until midnight, I suggest to go in the morning because then, sun rays can seep through the small cracks of the mountain, lightly brightening up the caves resulting in some out of this world photos. The best part about Qara Mountain is the freedom you are given, there are no limits to your adventure and this made the trip unforgettable.
title: Al-Qara Hill

content: It would be 3 stars - since the pool is unavailable to women (for a Thursday night to Saturday checkout ) and the breakfast buffet is an incredible disappointment... however, the household and maintenance staff are wonderful. In order to get room service at 10:30 am on Saturday I had to call the front desk (room service and concierge phones were not answered). But the service was quick. It's a nice hotel.. some of the pros: bed and pillows are super comfy, very clean, lots of tv channel options for English and arabic speakers (French channels too), there are wonderful beachfront restaurants nearby, rooms with sea views are very nice). Additional cons: parking is overcrowded, 7th floor lounge level - friends paid an extra $250 per night for the same room with access to a "lounge" - they found no added value. Check-in took a long time.
title: Sofitel Al Khobar The Corniche

content: One of the best experiences I've had in South KSA (Jazan region). The valley of Wadi Lajab is a canyon about 5 kilometers long, situated about 80 kms away from Jizan city. The most incredible feature of Wadi Lajab is the fact that it delivers fresh water more regularly than any other wadi in Saudi Arabia. There is a stream that runs at the bottom of the canyon! It is believed that Majnu from the famous "Layla Majnu" (in which the hero Majnu bin Qais dies) came from Wadi Lajab region. Piece of advice: First, you can't come here if you dont have a 4 wheel drive because this is a mountainous rocky area. Arrange for a jeep or any other 4 wheel drive vehicle. Second, bring your own snacks and water, because there isn't any available for many kilometers. Lastly, make sure you wear good shoes so you can climb up rocks and keep a spare pair with you. It's even more fun if you come with a whole lot of people. YOU MUST VISIT THIS PLACE. THANK ME LATER.
title: Wadi Lajab

content: يذكر المؤرخون أن الملكة العربية الشهيرة زنوبيا؛ التي حكمت تدمر بين 267 و272، غزت دومة الجندل، لكن قلعة المدينة كانت حصينة؛ حيث لم تتمكن من اقتحامها فعادت من حيث أتت، وقالت قولتها الشهيرة: "تمرد مارد وعز الأبلق". وفي كتاب "الجوف وادي النفاخ"، يذكر المؤلف أن الهدم والتدمير أصابا الجدار الخارجي للقلعة والأبراج بعد هجوم وقع عام 1270هـ. التقطت لقلعة أو قصر مارد الكثير من الصور، ومن أقدمها الصورة التي صوّرها ميجر هولت؛ عام 1922.

content: A very lovely green area. A large parameter to walk or run on the outside. Entrance fee is 12 SAR per adult. Not sure of the young fees though. Inside is a large green area suitable for a walk. Picnics are allowed. You can get your own food or buy from snack shops inside. The large lake showcases a dancing fountain every 1-2 hours after dusk. The times are a bit flexible.. so you'll have to wait to see. Kids play area is available with swings and slides. Though they'd enjoy running on the grass more. Down side is professional cameras are not allowed, which is a shame cuz its a lobely place to make memories. Yet you can take photos with your camera phone!!!

content: MoreSo recently we visited @nandossa , i wanted to visit this place from such a long time, i have heard about it alot and i must say this is the best place for chicken lover . . .Things we ordered . . * 3 full chicken wings It was so juicy and so scrumptious along with sauce * Chicken and pineapple skewers The chicken was so tender along with pineapple skewers , pita bread, yogurt dip and salsa. * Espatada alteza + 2 regular sides The chicken was so tasty and yummy. We orderd peri- peri chips and salad. * Drinks 1 fresh orange juice 1 refreshmint . . * Dessert Chocolate peanut butter stack . Nandos is very reasonable yet so scrumptious. Will definitely go again . I have become a huge fan of nandos. Highly recommend for chicken and spice lovers. . . Note :- prices are little high but taste is so so good.

content: One of the best five stars hotel in the city if not the best, we particularly liked the views from our deluxe room overlooking the marina. The room included breakfast which had various options ( e.g. omelettes, pancakes, pastries, cheeses and more ) to choose from. The hotel had various facilities like the swimming pool ( men only) and gym (separate ones, one for ladies and one for the gentlemen) Overall, customer service was great. The hotel management surprised us with sweets ( delegates tarts, macaroons and dates) every night of our stay. The hygiene level is on point, hand sanitizer everywhere and masks to stay safe from Covid-19. Our stay was memorable and will surely come back again
title: Bay La Sun Hotel & Marina ( KAEC )

content: More(Translated by Google) The Quba Mosque is the first mosque built in Islam and the first mosque built in the Prophet’s city. The Quba Mosque was built by the Prophet, may God’s prayers and peace be upon him, when he immigrated from Mecca to the city of Medina. Fahd bin Abdulaziz Al Saud laid the foundation stone for the recent expansion of the Quba Mosque in 1405, and the mosque was designed in its center, a large courtyard, and also the Quba Mosque has 4 minarets and contains 56 domes, the mosque’s land area is 13,500 square meters and the mosque’s building area is 5860 (Original) مسجد قباء هو اول مسجد بني في الاسلام واول مسجد بني في المدينه النبويه وبني مسجد قباء من قبل النبي صلي الله عليه وسلم وذالك حينما هاجر من مكه المكرمه الي المدينه المنوره وبعد ذاللك اهتمالمسلمن بعماره مسجد قباء فجدده عثمان ابن عفان ثم عمر بن عبدالعزيز وفي عهد الملك فهد بن عبدالعزيز ال سعود وضع حجر الاساس للتوسعه الاخيره في مسجد قباء عام 1405وقد صمم المسجد وفي اوسطه فناء واسع وايضا مسجد قباء له 4 ماذن ويحتوي علي 56 قبه ومساحه ارض المسجد 13500 متر مربع ومساحه مباني المسجد 5860

content: More(Translated by Google) The Holy Kaaba, the Muslim kiss A lofty building in the heart of the Holy Mosque of Mecca, to which the hearts of Muslims yearn for it, and it is the first house placed on earth to worship God alone, without a partner. And the Kaaba is called due to its cubic, which is its square and every tall building (the Kaaba). Al-Nawawi said that it was called because of its roundness and height, and it was said that it was originally squared. The relationship is close and eternal between the Holy Kaaba since its construction and its near geographical surroundings, and by that we mean the Sacred Mosque, and this contiguity between them has led to a consideration of the increase in the areas of the Grand Mosque since the dawn of the dawn of prophethood, and it followed that in a way that allows Muslims to perform their rituals in reverence and reassurance. There was no mention of the Grand Mosque before Islam and it is known only to circumnavigate circling the Holy Kaaba, because the pre-Islamic era did not include prayers performed around the Kaaba, but they used to circumambulate around it only, and the ignorant people used to sit around it in the morning and evening, using it to shelter from the sun. And God guided Abraham, peace be upon him, to the location of the Holy Kaaba, and ordered him to build it, so he built it, and called again, and said: “Lord, make this country safe.” Then he called in the third by saying: “So make the hearts of the people that they like and provide them with fruits so that they may be grateful.” Various peoples lived in it, and the giants succeeded in governing the Kaaba, Jirhm, Khuza'a, Quraysh, and others. The Kaaba was the object of veneration and reverence for the people and the governors of Makkah, they reconstruct it and renew its structure when needed, clothe it, and regard it as a pride and honor for them, until Islam came and increased its honor, urged to venerate it and purify it, and the Prophet - may God bless him and grant him peace - and the Companions after him. (Original) الكعبة المشرفة، قبلة المسلمين بناء شامخ في قلب الحرم المكي الشريف ، تهفو إليها قلوب المسلمين ، وهي أول بيت وضع في الأرض لعبادة الله وحده لا شريك له ، كما قال تعالى : " إن أول بيت وضع للناس للذي ببكة مباركًا وهدى للعالمين " ، وهي محط الأنظار وقبلة المسلمين . وسميت الكعبة نسبة لتكعيبها وهو تربيعها وكل بناء مرتفع ( كعبة ) وقال النووي سميت بذلك لاستدارتها وعلوها وقيل تربيعها في الأصل . والعلاقة وثيقة وأزلية بين الكعبة المشرفة منذ بنائها ومحيطها الجغرافي القريب، ونعني به المسجد الحرام وأدى هذا التجاور بينهما إلى النظر في زيادة مساحات المسجد الحرام منذ بزوغ فجر النبوة وماتلا ذلك بما يتيح للمسلمين أداء شعائرهم في خشوع وطمأنينة . ولم يكن هناك ذكر للمسجد الحرام قبل الإسلام والمتعارف عليه فقط مدار الطواف حول الكعبة المشرفة، لأن العصر الجاهلي لم يتضمن صلاة تؤدى حول الكعبة، بل كانوا يطوفون حولها فقط واعتاد الجاهليون الجلوس حولها في الصباح والمساء يستظلون بها من الشمس . وأرشد الله إبراهيم عليه السلام إلى مكان الكعبة المشرفة، وأمره ببنائها، فبناها، ودعا مرة أخرى، فقال : " رب اجعل هذا البلد آمنًا "، ثم دعا في الثالثة بقوله : " فاجعل أفئدة من الناس تهوى إليهم وارزقهم من الثمرات لعلهم يشكرون " . فسكنت فيه أقوام مختلفة، وتعاقبت على ولاية الكعبة العمالقة ، وجرهم ، وخزاعة ، وقريش ، وغيرهم . وكانت الكعبة موضع تعظيم وإجلال الناس والولاة على مكة، يعمرونها ويجددون بنيانها عند الحاجة، ويكسونها، ويحتسبونه فخرًا وتشريفًا لهم، حتى جاء الإسلام فزاد في تشريفها، وحث على تعظيمها، وتطهيرها، وكساها النبي - صلى الله عليه وسلم - والصحابة بعده .

content: I booked the hotel four months before the date of the stay, to celebrated our wedding anniversary and I put note on the reservation for my occasion. I ask for upgrade, he said no big difference between the rooms ! The luxury of the room in the bathroom for the deluxe room. After a while We found cockroach in the cabinet, and I request to change the room and they upgrade me. The breakfast unfortunately not for 5 stars hotel it’s like you open a can and put it in the dish. Room service (housekeeping) they are the best ever they care about small details. I didn’t think that I will re-experience with this hotel again and the front desk should be improved and the breakfast.

content: MoreThe best and beautiful place on the earth. Mecca is the birthplace of Muhammad. The Hira cave atop the Jabal al-Nur ("Mountain of Light") is just outside the city and is where Muslims believe the Quran was first revealed to Muhammad.[4] Visiting Mecca for the Hajj is an obligation upon all able Muslims. The Great Mosque of Mecca, known as the Masjid al-Haram, is home to the Ka'bah, believed by Muslims to have been built by Abraham and Ishmael, is one of Islam's holiest sites and the direction of prayer for all Muslims (qibla), cementing Mecca's significance in Islam.[5] Muslim rulers from in and around the region long tried to take the city and keep it in their control, and thus, much like most of the Hejaz region, the city has seen several regime changes. The city was finally conquered in the Saudi conquest of Hejaz by Ibn Saud and his allies in 1925. Since then, Mecca has seen a tremendous expansion in size and infrastructure, with newer, modern buildings such as the Abraj Al Bait, the world's fourth-tallest building and third-largest by floor area, towering over the Great Mosque. The Saudi government has also carried out the destruction of several historical structures and archaeological sites,[6] such as the Ajyad Fortress.[7][8][9] Non-Muslims (Kuffar) are strictly prohibited from entering the city.[10][11] Muslims from around the world visit the city, not only for the Hajj and Umrah pilgrimages, but also as tourists to visit regional landmarks such as the 'Aisha Mosque (Masjid 'Aisha) and the sites visited by pilgrims in the Hajj and 'Umrah. Mecca is now home to two of the most expensive buildings in the world, the Masjid al-Haram, valued at 100 billion US dollars, and the Abraj al-Bait complex, valued at 15 billion US dollars. Under the Saudi government, Mecca is governed by the Mecca Regional Municipality, a municipal council of 14 locally elected members headed by the mayor (called Amin in Arabic) appointed by the Saudi government. As of May 2015, the mayor of the city is Dr. Osama bin Fadhel Al-Barr.[12][13] The City of Mecca amanah, which constitutes Mecca and the surrounding region, is the capital of the Mecca Province, which includes the neighboring cities of Jeddah and Ta'if, even though Jeddah is considerably larger in population compared to Mecca. The Provincial Governor of the province from 16 May 2007 is Prince Khalid bin Faisal Al Saud.[14] Copy from Wikipedia

content: More(Translated by Google) Jabal Al-Qarah, also known as Jabal Al-Shabaan, is located between the village of Al-Tuwaytheer and the village of Al-Qarah in Al-Ahsa Governorate, in the Eastern Province of Saudi Arabia. The mountain is one of the most prominent natural tourist attractions in Al-Ahsa, and it was registered in the World Heritage List in 2018 after the Al-Ahsa Oasis was included in the list. The mountain is located 15 kilometers east of Al-Hofuf. It contains caves or so-called caves among the people of Al-Ahsa. Some of its caves, such as the Archaeb Cave, have a moderate, almost constant temperature throughout the year. Entrance ticket price is 50 riyals (Original) جبل القارة ويُعرَف أيضاً بجبل الشبعان يقع بين قرية التويثير وقرية القارة بمحافظة الأحساء، في المنطقة الشرقية من المملكة العربية السعودية. يُعد الجبل من أبرز المعالم السياحية الطبيعية في الأحساء وقد سُجل في لائحة التراث العالمي عام 2018م بعد ضم واحة الأحساء إلى اللائحة. يبعد الجبل مسافة 15 كيلومتراً شرق مدينة الهفوف. ويحتوي على كهوفٍ أو ما يسمى بالمغاراتِ بين أهالي الأحساء. تتميز بعض مغاراته مثل مغارة النشاب بأن لها درجة حرارة معتدلة شبه ثابتة طوال العام. سعر تذكرة الدخول 50 ريال

content: MoreMasjid Al-Ghamamah is one of the oldest mosques in Medina, Saudi Arabia, located in the place believed to be where the Prophet Muhammad ﷺ performed an Eid prayer in the year 631. The mosque is one of the historical relics of Medina. The mosque was built during the reign of the Caliph Umar bin Abdul Aziz between the hijri calendar of 86 to 93 and later by many Muslim rulers. Masjid Al Ghamāmah is located northwest of the Prophets Mosque. It took its name after the clouds shaded the Prophet ﷺ‎ while he was delivering his sermon. It was rebuilt at the time of the Ottoman Sultan, Abdul Majīd in the year 1275 A.H./ 1859 A.D which is preserved until now. The Mosque is of a rectangular shape built with Black Basalt stones and roofed with 11 domes. The domes and walls are white on the inside whereas the pillars and arcs are black which gives Masjid Al Ghamāmah a unique appearance.
title: Masjid Al Ghamamah

content: It was convenient stay, the check in and check out was normal. The room was good and spacious, with decent cleaning etc. Though furniture was bit too old and working table and associated chair were not optimum for work desk. I dream that one of these days the hotels will put adjustable height tables to meet modern day needs of business travelers. Two things were not good, 1) While room inside was neat and clean, the windows were really dirty, so you dare not to open the curtain. 2) Staff assigned to take body temp. was non serious and not doing his job, this means there is no real monitoring of temp. of visitors to the hotel. It was just a shame.
title: Crowne Plaza al Khobar

content: جربت الفندق ثلاث مرات تقريبا الفندق ممتاز جدا وخدمة الموظفين ممتازة جدا ونظام غرف الفندق مثل الشقة غرفة وصالة ودورة مياه مناسبة جدا للعوائل او اكثر من شخصين، وكل شي ممتاز ورائع لكن عندي بعض الملاحظات السلبية: حجم شاشات التلفزيون صغير جدا ومقاربة لحجم شاشة الكمبيوتر. ضعف الضخ بدورات المياه تحتاج وقت طويل عشان امتلاء حوض الاستحمام. لا يوجد عازل بالغرف نسمع سوالف الناس وضحكهم. لا يتم توفير كامل الاغراض الفندقية مثل احذية الحمام وروب الاستحمام والمناديل الا بالطلب ، المفروض متوفرة مسبقا وبدون طلب. ادوات البار الكاسات الزجاجية والغلاية قديمة جدا ومتسخة وبشكل عام الفندق ممتاز جدا ومختلف بشكل مميز عن باقي الفنادق الاخرى

content: MoreQara Mountain is the perfect place to visit when you are seeking family adventure. On the outside, the view of the mountains are breathtaking. Then on the inside, there are many tunnels and exploring through them, was incredibly fun. Even though, they are open until midnight, I suggest to go in the morning because then, sun rays can seep through the small cracks of the mountain, lightly brightening up the caves resulting in some out of this world photos. The best part about Qara Mountain is the freedom you are given, there are no limits to your adventure and this made the trip unforgettable.

content: MoreThe Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque (Arabic: جَامِع ٱلشَّيْخ زَايِد ٱلْكَبِيْر‎, romanized: Jāmiʿ Ash-Shaykh Zāyid Al-Kabīr) is located in Abu Dhabi, the capital city of the United Arab Emirates.[2] The largest mosque in the country, it is the key place of worship for daily, Friday and Eid prayers. During Eid, it may be visited by more than 41,000 people.[2] Sheikh Zayed Grand mosque جَامِع ٱلشَّيْخ زَايِد ٱلْكَبِيْر ￼ Sheikh Zayed Mosque as seen from the courtyard. ReligionAffiliationIslamBranch/traditionSunni Islam (Malikite)OwnershipGovernmentLocationLocationAbu Dhabi, U.A.E. ￼ ￼ Location in the United Arab Emirates Geographic coordinates24.412°N 54.474°EArchitectureArchitect(s)Yusef Abdelki of Halcrow Group[1]TypeMosqueGroundbreaking1996Completed20 December 2007Construction cost2 billion dirhams (US$545 million)SpecificationsCapacityover 41000Length420 m (1,380 ft)Width290 m (950 ft)Dome(s)82 domes of seven different sizesDome height (outer)85 m (279 ft)Dome dia. (outer)32.2 m (106 ft)Minaret(s)4Minaret height107 m (351 ft)Websiteمركز جامع الشيخ زايد الكبير HistoryEdit The Grand Mosque was constructed between 1996 and 2007.[3] It was designed by Syrian architect Yousef Abdelky.[4] The building complex measures approximately 290 by 420 m (950 by 1,380 ft), covering an area of more than 12 hectares (30 acres), excluding exterior landscaping and vehicle parking. The main axis of the building is rotated about 11° south of true west, aligning it in the direction of the Kaaba in Mecca, Saudi Arabia. The project was launched by the late president of the United Arab Emirates (UAE), Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan Al Nahyan, who wanted to establish a structure that would unite the cultural diversity of the Islamic world with the historical and modern values of architecture and art.[5] In 2004, Sheikh Zayed died and was buried in the courtyard of the mosque. Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque Center (SZGMC) offices are located in the west minarets. SZGMC manages the day-to-day operations and serves as a center of learning and discovery through its educational cultural activities and visitor programs. The library, located in the northeast minaret, serves the community with classic books and publications addressing a range of Islamic subjects: sciences, civilization, calligraphy, the arts, and coins, including some rare publications dating back more than 200 years. The collection comprises material in a broad range of languages, including Arabic, English, French, Italian, Spanish, German, and Korean. For two years running, it was voted the world's second favorite landmark by TripAdvisor.[6] Design and constructionEdit The design of the Sheikh Zayed Mosque has been inspired by Persian, Mughal, and the Alexandrian Mosque of Abu al-Abbas al-Mursi Mosque in Egypt, also the Indo-Islamic mosque architecture, particularly the Badshahi Mosque in Lahore, Pakistan being direct influences. The dome layout and floorplan of the mosque was inspired by the Badshahi Mosque. Its archways are quintessentially Moorish, and its minarets classically Arab. Under lead contractor Impregilo (Italy), more than 3,000 workers and 38 sub-contracting companies were conscripted in its construction. The mosque was completed under a second contract by a Joint Venture between ACC and Six Construct (part of BESIX ) between 2004 and 2007.[7][8][9] Natural materials were chosen for much of its design and construction due to their long-lasting qualities, including marble stone, gold, semi-precious stones, crystals and ceramics. Artisans and materials came from many countries including India, Italy, Germany, Egypt, Turkey, Morocco, Pakistan, Malaysia, Iran, China, United Kingdom, New Zealand, North Macedonia and the UAE.[citation needed] Dimensions and statisticsEdit The mosque is large enough to accommodate over 40,000 worshippers, while the main prayer hall can hold over 7,000. There are two smaller prayer halls, with a capacity of 1,500 each, one of which is the women's prayer hall.[2] There are four minarets on the four corners of the courtyard which rise about 107 m
title: Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque

content: Although the food looks good, it doesn’t taste as good. I expected much more for the price paid. the service was subpar and on the low end since I kept asking the waiters for things to bring and they just nod and ignore my requests. What makes this place different than other steak havens? Live cooking show! Sadly, I have visited this place multiple times for their cooking show options but everytime I visited I couldn’t get such service either because the show chef isn’t around or the show grill is undergoing “maintenance” which is a bummer. The food is okay, not amazing but okay. Prices are shot through the roof for no apparent reason since I could get a similar steak at another restaurant for 20-30 riyals cheaper.

content: The hotel is situated on strategic location. However, my experience in this hotel was very disappointing. The room was dusty and the carpet, bed linen, and towels are full of hair. The room service menu is limited and the quality of food was below average. At Your Service, the guest service center where you should inquire and place orders for housekeeping and in room dining, was not available most of the time, you have to dial the number for several times until someone picks up the phone, I've tried it in different timing and the result is almost the same every time. On the other hand, the team members that I have encountered with were in general polite, supportive, and friendly with minor exceptions. I guess, the hotel's management must go back to the basics in hospitality, and ensure that the rooms are clean, food quality is good, and service team is available to answer the phone. By the way, in my second week, I have received a call from the guest relations asking about my feedback about the hotel, and I've reported everything, but nothing has really changed, though, my stay at the hotel was a lengthy one and I had no other choice but to stay there for the whole period.

content: MoreIt's was my first time during this Covid time. The arrangements were superb. Not very crowdy. Very systematic approach. You have to have a bus ticket, park your car at Kudai parking and get into the tent. Show your permit and they will give you a ticket to get in the bus. . Bus will take you to the Haram, it will dropped you off around 700 to 800 meters aways from Haram. Then you have to walk. Upon reaching at your authorized door guard will check your permit and let you through. Thermal cameras are installed for covid scanning. The way will take you straight to mataf. Mataf area is marked by various colors of tapes. Very convenient and easy to perform. After mataf pray two rakat sunnah and move to safa and marwa. Upon completion of Saii you will return back to your entrance door and move back to kudai bus station. Barber shops are open in clock tower building. Keep your Ticket with you. As it requires to show when you ride back. Bus then will take you back to kudai parking.

The Jawathi, Gotha, or Juatha Mosque is located in Al-Ahsa Governorate, in eastern Saudi Arabia, and the mosque, which is located within a park known by the same name, is about 17 kilometers northeast of Al-Hofuf. This mosque was built during the era of the Prophet Muhammad, peace be upon him, and the inhabitants of the country of Bahrain, Banu Abd Qais, who were the ones who initiated their conversion to Islam willingly, not by compulsion, and the Prophet praised the people of these lands by saying (Honor your brothers, for they are like you people who converted to Islam voluntarily and not involuntarily), and the rules of this mosque are still List to our current time Its origin is from the corpses of the man, if he panics, it is as if they would return to it when they were terrified, they called it that. This is supported by the presence of a fortress on the site, and the site of Jawahi now, a site of sand dunes, and it has depressions in which evidence of old settlement and buildings are broken. Active settlement in the location of the cumulative hills within the scope of the sand reservation project, the National Park in Al-Ahsa, where there are groups of archaeological hills covered by sand and spread over them many varieties of pottery and ceramic fragments and types of colored and white transparent glass The mosque is characterized by a unique architectural style, and it was built from jar and clay mortar, and its roof is made of sandalwood and has a total area of ​​about 206.5 m and accommodates about 170 worshipers, and the mosque consists of a prayer house containing three corridors, and the mosque also contains a share for bullying, and a room used as a warehouse, The mosque contains three towers that are placed on the outer pillars of the mosque (Original) مغلق حاليا . مسجد جواثى أو جوثا أو جواثا، يقع في محافظة الأحساء شرق المملكة العربية السعودية، ويبعد المسجد الذي يقع ضمن متنزه يعرف بالاسم نفسه، نحو 17 كيلومتراً شمال شرق مدينة الهفوف. بني هذا المسجد في عهد النبي محمد عليه السلام وتشرف ببنائه سكان بلاد إقليم البحرين بنو عبد قيس وهم الذين بادروا بإسلامهم طوعاً لا كرهاً وقد مدح النبي أهل هذه الديار بقوله (أكرموا أخوانكم فإنهم أشبه الناس بكم أسلموا طوعاً لا كرهاً)، ولا تزال قواعد هذا المسجد قائمة إلى وقتنا الحالي جواثى أصله من جأث الرجل إذا فزع فكأنهم لما كانوا يرجعون إليها عند الفزع سموها بذلك وهذا يؤيده وجود حصن بالموقع وموقع جواثى الآن موقع كثبان رملية، وبه منخفضات تظهر فيها دلائل استيطان قديم ومبان مندثرة، ربما تكون بقايا جواثى الأمس أو جزءا منها، وتظهر بالموقع دلائل استقرار نشط في موضع التلال التراكمية ضمن نطاق مشروع حجز الرمال المنتزه الوطني بالأحساء، فتوجد بالموقع مجموعات من التلال الأثرية التي تغطيها الرمال وتنتشر فوقها أصناف عديدة من الكسر الفخارية والخزفية وأنواع من الزجاج الملون والأبيض الشفاف يتميز المسجد بطراز معماري فريد، وقد تم بناؤه من ال جر ومونة الطين، وسقفه من خشب السندل وتبلغ مساحته الكلية نحو 206.5م ويتسع لنحو 170مصلياً، ويتكون المسجد من بيت الصلاة يحتوي على ثلاث أروقة ، كما يحتوي المسجد على حصة للتنمر، وغرفة تستخدم كمستودع، ويحتوي المسجد على ثلاث أبراج موضوعه على اركان المسجد الخارجية
